1
00:00:02,856 --> 00:00:05,159
♪

2
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:06,395
[engines revving]

3
00:00:06,396 --> 00:00:07,898
[Chester Arborday]
<i>It's the final lap</i>

4
00:00:07,899 --> 00:00:09,667
<i>of the Springfield
Little Grand Prix,</i>

5
00:00:09,668 --> 00:00:12,273
<i>and the karts are tighter
than a royal corgi's collar</i>

6
00:00:12,274 --> 00:00:14,913
<i>as they head into Lard Lad turn.</i>

7
00:00:17,751 --> 00:00:19,620
<i>We have contact! Things
are looking bloody grim</i>

8
00:00:19,621 --> 00:00:24,196
<i>for the rising star
of KF-1... Kids Formula One...</i>

9
00:00:24,197 --> 00:00:26,034
<i>Lisa Simpson.</i>

10
00:00:26,035 --> 00:00:27,938
<i>Simpson spins out!</i>

11
00:00:27,939 --> 00:00:28,941
[all gasp]

12
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:34,116
[Arborday]
<i>Look at that icy calm.</i>

13
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,319
<i>Clearly, this pre-tween dynamo</i>

14
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,426
<i>has never felt
a modicum of unease</i>

15
00:00:38,427 --> 00:00:41,665
<i>in any automobile.</i>

16
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,202
Dad!

17
00:00:43,203 --> 00:00:45,106
You're gonna hit the median.

18
00:00:45,107 --> 00:00:47,076
All part of the plan.

19
00:00:47,077 --> 00:00:48,078
[Lisa exclaiming]

20
00:00:48,079 --> 00:00:48,846
[grunts]

21
00:00:48,847 --> 00:00:52,720
[whimpering]

22
00:00:52,721 --> 00:00:54,391
Aah!

23
00:00:54,392 --> 00:00:57,230
Bart, soccer practice.
Go, go, go!

24
00:00:57,231 --> 00:00:57,899
Whoa!

25
00:00:57,900 --> 00:01:00,670
Goal...!

26
00:01:01,472 --> 00:01:05,747
Dad, please, you don't
have to hurry like this.

27
00:01:06,783 --> 00:01:08,785
Cut me off? I cut you off!

28
00:01:08,786 --> 00:01:12,660
[Lisa] He didn't cut you off,
he's just driving!

29
00:01:12,661 --> 00:01:14,264
Hope you like brakes
because today

30
00:01:14,265 --> 00:01:18,138
it's all-you-can-eat, baby.

31
00:01:18,139 --> 00:01:20,275
[Lisa exclaims]

32
00:01:20,276 --> 00:01:22,246
Dad, stop...

33
00:01:22,247 --> 00:01:23,984
brake checking...

34
00:01:23,985 --> 00:01:25,519
him.

35
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,855
- [groans]
- Speed bump, sweetie.

36
00:01:26,856 --> 00:01:28,125
We're gonna get a little air.

37
00:01:29,095 --> 00:01:30,596
[squeals]

38
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:35,773
Ugh.
I hate when we're early.

39
00:01:35,774 --> 00:01:38,011
Mr. and Mrs. Simpson,
as you know,

40
00:01:38,012 --> 00:01:39,714
Lisa has been feeling
a lack of control,

41
00:01:39,715 --> 00:01:42,453
which feeds
her generalized anxiety.

42
00:01:42,454 --> 00:01:45,159
I know, I know.
It's getting worse.

43
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,728
Her twitch jumped eyes.

44
00:01:46,729 --> 00:01:50,002
She used to be a righty.
Where will it jump next?

45
00:01:50,003 --> 00:01:51,404
Mm...

46
00:01:51,405 --> 00:01:54,444
Mom, do you have to do that now?

47
00:01:54,445 --> 00:01:56,381
I knit when I'm worried.

48
00:01:56,382 --> 00:01:59,387
Marge is
our family designated worrier,

49
00:01:59,388 --> 00:02:01,625
which frees me up
to be the cool dad.

50
00:02:01,626 --> 00:02:03,763
Plus, I get
some awesome worry swag.

51
00:02:04,731 --> 00:02:07,871
Marge made this when Bart
swallowed a nine-volt battery

52
00:02:07,872 --> 00:02:10,610
and I had to track it
with a stud finder.

53
00:02:13,016 --> 00:02:13,550
Well... [clears throat]

54
00:02:13,683 --> 00:02:15,452
I asked you both here today

55
00:02:15,453 --> 00:02:18,459
because Lisa made
a significant breakthrough

56
00:02:18,460 --> 00:02:20,095
at her last session.

57
00:02:20,096 --> 00:02:21,364
Oh, that's wonderful.

58
00:02:21,365 --> 00:02:24,370
Doctor, I can't
thank you enough.

59
00:02:24,371 --> 00:02:26,607
This is such a relief.

60
00:02:26,608 --> 00:02:30,315
Lisa, whatever it is
that's causing your anxiety,

61
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:32,486
we will walk through hell
to fix it.

62
00:02:32,487 --> 00:02:36,461
Well, Mr. Simpson,
it's your driving.

63
00:02:36,462 --> 00:02:40,570
What did you just say to me?

64
00:02:42,407 --> 00:02:44,277
Well, Dad, um, you know,

65
00:02:44,278 --> 00:02:46,347
you can be a little aggressive
behind the wheel.

66
00:02:46,348 --> 00:02:49,454
I drive at the speed of traffic.

67
00:02:49,455 --> 00:02:51,158
You can at least listen
to Doctor...

68
00:02:51,159 --> 00:02:53,561
Lenny thinks I drive cool.

69
00:02:53,562 --> 00:02:55,332
Everything is always my fault.

70
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,268
Well, two can play at that game.

71
00:02:56,269 --> 00:02:59,040
I say you're a terrible driver.

72
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:01,444
I'm much faster than you.
[grunts]

73
00:03:01,445 --> 00:03:03,582
- [footsteps departing]
- [car door closes]

74
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:04,817
- [car skids away]
- [vehicles honking]

75
00:03:04,818 --> 00:03:08,025
- Doctor, I'm so sorry about...
- [phone rings]

76
00:03:08,626 --> 00:03:10,563
<i>You have some nerve</i>

77
00:03:10,564 --> 00:03:12,766
<i>putting these thoughts
in my daughter's head.</i>

78
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:15,406
Mr. Simpson, can we please
continue this conversation

79
00:03:15,407 --> 00:03:17,276
when you're not driving?

80
00:03:17,277 --> 00:03:18,645
<i>[siren wailing]</i>

81
00:03:18,646 --> 00:03:21,284
<i>Go around. Go around.</i>

82
00:03:21,285 --> 00:03:24,123
<i>Aah! [shrieking]</i>

83
00:03:24,124 --> 00:03:25,526
[Lisa and Marge] Aah!

84
00:03:25,527 --> 00:03:27,362
Did you flip over?

85
00:03:27,363 --> 00:03:29,634
<i>I'm not the one on trial here.</i>

86
00:03:30,503 --> 00:03:31,672
<i>Your trial's in two weeks.</i>

87
00:03:31,673 --> 00:03:34,912
<i>Hey, Doc!
Great work with Ralphie.</i>

88
00:03:34,913 --> 00:03:37,716
<i>We can keep aluminum foil
in the house again.</i>

89
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:40,256
<i>Uh, we'll pick this up later.</i>

90
00:03:41,325 --> 00:03:42,260
[whimpers]

91
00:03:42,261 --> 00:03:44,697
Doctor, what can we do?

92
00:03:44,698 --> 00:03:47,070
Well, I have one idea.

93
00:03:48,406 --> 00:03:51,744
Here, we practice
immersion therapy.

94
00:03:51,745 --> 00:03:53,815
We expose patients
to their phobias

95
00:03:53,816 --> 00:03:57,256
so their habituated response
can decrease over time.

96
00:03:57,257 --> 00:03:58,425
[whimpering]

97
00:03:58,426 --> 00:04:00,562
[stammers] Monsters.

98
00:04:00,563 --> 00:04:02,600
Monsters all. Ow!

99
00:04:02,601 --> 00:04:05,506
So, he's afraid of germs
on toilet seats.

100
00:04:05,507 --> 00:04:07,710
No, he's afraid
of rotisserie chicken.

101
00:04:07,711 --> 00:04:10,682
Lisa, if we can
use this exposure treatment

102
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:12,653
to get you comfortable in cars,

103
00:04:12,654 --> 00:04:15,025
that might help you
overcome your other anxieties.

104
00:04:15,026 --> 00:04:17,696
Okay, I'll do whatever it takes.

105
00:04:17,697 --> 00:04:20,635
Well, I must warn you,
it won't be fun.

106
00:04:20,636 --> 00:04:22,875
[kids shouting]

107
00:04:25,747 --> 00:04:27,382
By driving a go-kart,

108
00:04:27,383 --> 00:04:28,685
you can feel
a measure of control

109
00:04:28,686 --> 00:04:30,222
in your relationship
with motor vehicles.

110
00:04:30,223 --> 00:04:32,292
I don't want to drive.

111
00:04:32,293 --> 00:04:33,262
Just put me back on the pills.

112
00:04:33,263 --> 00:04:34,330
No wait, no pills.

113
00:04:34,331 --> 00:04:35,833
They make me feel nothing.

114
00:04:35,834 --> 00:04:37,603
But my room
has never been cleaner.

115
00:04:37,604 --> 00:04:38,539
But I never laugh.

116
00:04:38,539 --> 00:04:39,508
But there's a calm in that.

117
00:04:39,509 --> 00:04:42,580
But the sound
of the grass growing is loud!

118
00:04:42,581 --> 00:04:44,584
Lisa!
It's going to be all right.

119
00:04:44,585 --> 00:04:48,325
Take a breath
and give it a little gas.

120
00:04:48,326 --> 00:04:50,262
No!
I am not doing this.

121
00:04:50,263 --> 00:04:52,033
I am putting my foot down.

122
00:04:53,169 --> 00:04:54,370
Aah! See?

123
00:04:54,371 --> 00:04:56,474
I could have killed a tire.

124
00:04:56,475 --> 00:04:59,447
[sighs]
Well, we tried.

125
00:04:59,448 --> 00:05:00,649
I am out of here.

126
00:05:00,650 --> 00:05:02,520
Gonna get this
back to the starting area,

127
00:05:02,521 --> 00:05:04,491
and...

128
00:05:04,492 --> 00:05:07,363
Oh... That wasn't so bad.

129
00:05:07,364 --> 00:05:10,068
[chuckles, whoops]

130
00:05:10,069 --> 00:05:10,670
Zippy.

131
00:05:10,671 --> 00:05:12,908
We can try other approaches.

132
00:05:12,909 --> 00:05:15,212
They're making up new therapies
all the time.

133
00:05:15,213 --> 00:05:18,518
Mm. I really hoped
this one would work.

134
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:20,489
It's working!

135
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:22,459
I'm finally in control.

136
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:24,230
Oh!
Doctor, you cured her.

137
00:05:24,231 --> 00:05:26,368
We don't like to use
the word "cure."

138
00:05:26,369 --> 00:05:28,438
[whooping, laughing]

139
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:30,075
But I'm okay with "miracle."

140
00:05:30,076 --> 00:05:31,178
[whooping]

141
00:05:36,406 --> 00:05:39,545
[Arborday]
<i>Johannes on Schwarzvalder III</i>

142
00:05:39,546 --> 00:05:40,881
<i>cuts that turn
sharper than his mother</i>

143
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,150
<i>cuts the crust off
his egg and cress sandwiches.</i>

144
00:05:42,151 --> 00:05:43,519
♪

145
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,824
<i>He might hit 30 miles an hour!</i>

146
00:05:46,993 --> 00:05:51,035
<i>One small slipup means
a playdate with disaster...</i>

147
00:05:52,371 --> 00:05:54,576
<i>...unsupervised!</i>

148
00:06:05,330 --> 00:06:07,333
After dominating local races,

149
00:06:07,334 --> 00:06:10,641
Lisa Simpson will
make her debut in KF-1...

150
00:06:10,642 --> 00:06:14,314
the top international
go-kart circuit.

151
00:06:14,315 --> 00:06:16,185
<i>For the first time,
race fans worldwide</i>

152
00:06:16,186 --> 00:06:17,721
<i>will be able to witness</i>

153
00:06:17,722 --> 00:06:21,027
<i>Lisa's steely confidence
on the track.</i>

154
00:06:21,028 --> 00:06:22,330
I can't wait to get out there.

155
00:06:22,331 --> 00:06:24,401
For me, it's not about
winning or losing,

156
00:06:24,402 --> 00:06:25,771
it's about control.

157
00:06:25,772 --> 00:06:29,444
I used to be this big bundle
of worry and anxiety,

158
00:06:29,445 --> 00:06:31,314
<i>but on the track,
the world is going so fast,</i>

159
00:06:31,315 --> 00:06:34,855
<i>yet I am in complete command.</i>

160
00:06:34,856 --> 00:06:37,093
<i>The stillness
at the center of power.</i>

161
00:06:37,094 --> 00:06:39,063
I feel it everywhere.

162
00:06:39,064 --> 00:06:42,136
The other day,
I got my first A-minus ever

163
00:06:42,137 --> 00:06:44,207
on a test, no biggie.

164
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:46,277
Uh-oh.
Am I allowed to do that?

165
00:06:46,278 --> 00:06:48,482
[weak chuckle]
Will I lose more points?

166
00:06:48,483 --> 00:06:50,152
Does anyone have tape?

167
00:06:50,153 --> 00:06:52,591
Lisa is very good at her job

168
00:06:52,592 --> 00:06:55,864
of driving around and around.

169
00:06:55,865 --> 00:06:59,070
Her unshakable demeanor
has everyone asking

170
00:06:59,071 --> 00:07:02,109
where did this fearless phenom
come from?

171
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:05,082
Is she the scion
of a Greek shipping magnate?

172
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,520
Or the scion of
a Dutch shipping magnate?

173
00:07:07,521 --> 00:07:09,458
Just what nationality of magnate

174
00:07:09,459 --> 00:07:11,996
is she the scion of?

175
00:07:11,997 --> 00:07:15,202
The truth is she's from
an obscure racing backwater

176
00:07:15,203 --> 00:07:18,308
called... and I hope
I'm pronouncing this correctly...

177
00:07:18,309 --> 00:07:19,979
America.

178
00:07:19,980 --> 00:07:23,252
Her mother is a housewife
with no family fortune

179
00:07:23,253 --> 00:07:24,855
or rich dead husband.

180
00:07:24,856 --> 00:07:27,192
Her pathetic existence
peppered only

181
00:07:27,193 --> 00:07:29,899
with the mildest of victories.

182
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:32,069
Found it.

183
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:34,542
A life squandered.

184
00:07:34,543 --> 00:07:37,446
Lisa's father...
a bald, simpering,

185
00:07:37,447 --> 00:07:40,654
morbidly obese
drain on society...

186
00:07:40,655 --> 00:07:43,526
has been sentenced
to community service

187
00:07:43,527 --> 00:07:46,397
for a reckless driving
conviction.

188
00:07:46,398 --> 00:07:48,168
Am I going to look okay
in this show?

189
00:07:48,169 --> 00:07:50,373
I don't see how.

190
00:07:50,374 --> 00:07:51,943
- Oh!
- [cheering]

191
00:07:51,944 --> 00:07:53,846
D'oh!

192
00:07:53,847 --> 00:07:55,650
And despite
her dollar-store upbringing,

193
00:07:55,651 --> 00:07:59,725
Lisa Simpson stands poised
for international glory

194
00:07:59,726 --> 00:08:02,797
in this fall's KF-1
karting season,

195
00:08:02,798 --> 00:08:05,202
which coincidentally
will take place

196
00:08:05,203 --> 00:08:07,941
in her hometown of Springfield.

197
00:08:07,942 --> 00:08:11,047
We are happy to welcome
these wealthy child racers

198
00:08:11,048 --> 00:08:14,020
and their smoking-hot
trophy moms.

199
00:08:14,021 --> 00:08:15,057
[man]
Oh, yes!

200
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:18,796
European racing teams have
descended upon Springfield.

201
00:08:18,797 --> 00:08:21,434
And as always, the crew to beat

202
00:08:21,435 --> 00:08:24,642
is Italy's Team Dooshé.

203
00:08:24,643 --> 00:08:27,647
<i>Their charismatic star
is Paolo Paoletti...</i>

204
00:08:27,648 --> 00:08:31,956
<i>son of tracksuit mogul
Fila Fendi Paoletti...</i>

205
00:08:31,957 --> 00:08:36,197
<i>in the number seven Children's
Strength Tylenol kart.</i>

206
00:08:36,198 --> 00:08:38,335
[Italian accent] America is such

207
00:08:38,336 --> 00:08:41,340
a wonderfully
disgusting country.

208
00:08:41,341 --> 00:08:44,447
All the guns
and the billhillies,

209
00:08:44,448 --> 00:08:47,219
and all of the television shows
about Chicago.

210
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:50,627
The fire, the police,

211
00:08:50,628 --> 00:08:54,702
the man bear who makes
the beef sandwich.

212
00:08:54,703 --> 00:08:57,841
Oh, Paolo love. Boof.

213
00:08:57,842 --> 00:09:00,547
In a setback to
their jet-setting lifestyles,

214
00:09:00,548 --> 00:09:03,452
Paolo and the other
European go-karters

215
00:09:03,453 --> 00:09:04,556
must attend public school

216
00:09:04,656 --> 00:09:10,065
under the watchful eye of
broken, faceless bureaucrats.

217
00:09:10,066 --> 00:09:11,535
I have a face.

218
00:09:11,536 --> 00:09:13,304
Even though these kids
are impossibly wealthy,

219
00:09:13,305 --> 00:09:14,574
I think they'll fit right in.

220
00:09:14,575 --> 00:09:17,146
- They didn't.
- How do you know?

221
00:09:17,147 --> 00:09:18,214
It hasn't happened yet.

222
00:09:18,215 --> 00:09:19,585
But then it did.

223
00:09:19,586 --> 00:09:23,526
Hey, I asked
for vitello alla caper.

224
00:09:23,527 --> 00:09:26,063
What is this?

225
00:09:26,064 --> 00:09:27,768
Beanie weenies.

226
00:09:27,769 --> 00:09:30,974
Why do you hate my mouth?

227
00:09:30,975 --> 00:09:31,342
Huh?

228
00:09:31,343 --> 00:09:35,349
Why? [cries]

229
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:37,720
[Bart]
<i>Look at that sad foreign kid.</i>

230
00:09:37,721 --> 00:09:41,629
<i>He just needs a regular American
to reach out</i>

231
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,599
<i>and take advantage of him.</i>

232
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,368
Is there some problem here?

233
00:09:44,369 --> 00:09:47,273
This rectangle lady

234
00:09:47,274 --> 00:09:49,612
is trying to poison Paolo.

235
00:09:49,613 --> 00:09:51,381
Dry your eyes, Pinocchio.

236
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,418
I'm the guy that can make stuff
happen around here.

237
00:09:53,419 --> 00:09:56,692
If just might cost you a little.

238
00:09:56,693 --> 00:09:57,760
Whatever it takes.

239
00:09:57,761 --> 00:09:58,863
I give you one of each color.

240
00:09:58,864 --> 00:10:02,003
Purple, blue, green,
purple again.

241
00:10:03,206 --> 00:10:04,474
Mmm!

242
00:10:04,475 --> 00:10:06,612
<i>Delizioso.</i>

243
00:10:06,613 --> 00:10:10,787
Finally, somebody around here
with no accent.

244
00:10:10,788 --> 00:10:13,424
Mwah. Bartolomeo,
you make Paolo so happy.

245
00:10:13,425 --> 00:10:17,501
[sighs] You are Team Dooshé now.

246
00:10:17,502 --> 00:10:20,640
I'm make it rain on you.

247
00:10:20,641 --> 00:10:22,343
Boof, boof, boof, boof!

248
00:10:23,613 --> 00:10:24,714
[announcer]
<i>Gentlekids,</i>

249
00:10:24,715 --> 00:10:27,621
<i>start your two-stroke engines.</i>

250
00:10:27,622 --> 00:10:28,823
I can't believe it,

251
00:10:28,824 --> 00:10:32,296
my girl's first international
go-kart race.

252
00:10:32,297 --> 00:10:34,267
Did you put on sunblock?

253
00:10:34,268 --> 00:10:35,603
I'm in a fireproof suit.

254
00:10:35,604 --> 00:10:37,039
Oh, your father's here.

255
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:39,778
He's finished
with his community service.

256
00:10:39,779 --> 00:10:41,949
He can finally watch me race.

257
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:44,688
I wouldn't miss seeing
my little Danica Patrick

258
00:10:44,689 --> 00:10:46,659
for all the Jolly Ranchers
in the piñata.

259
00:10:46,660 --> 00:10:50,901
[chuckles]
The kids never check the legs.

260
00:10:55,043 --> 00:10:57,714
Now, honey,
I know they're going fast,

261
00:10:57,715 --> 00:11:00,385
but I'm sure Lisa's safe.

262
00:11:00,386 --> 00:11:02,725
There's nothing to worry about.

263
00:11:02,726 --> 00:11:03,993
Oh, I'm not worried.

264
00:11:03,994 --> 00:11:06,599
Come on, you got to be
a little worried.

265
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:09,504
Nope. I've seen Lisa race
a dozen times.

266
00:11:09,505 --> 00:11:12,042
She's really good
and she's safe.

267
00:11:12,043 --> 00:11:14,013
But-but you're the family's
designated worrier.

268
00:11:14,014 --> 00:11:16,986
If you're not worried, that
means there's a worry vacuum

269
00:11:16,987 --> 00:11:20,928
that I have to fill,
and vacuuming is also your job.

270
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:25,435
Oh, my God,
look how fast she's going.

271
00:11:25,436 --> 00:11:27,574
I'm not concerned in the least.

272
00:11:27,575 --> 00:11:29,410
And me am concerned in the most.

273
00:11:29,411 --> 00:11:31,849
I need the stress yarn.

274
00:11:31,850 --> 00:11:34,020
Relax, Homie, she's winning.

275
00:11:34,021 --> 00:11:36,892
Which means she's going faster
than everybody else.

276
00:11:36,893 --> 00:11:37,762
What am I even knitting?

277
00:11:37,763 --> 00:11:40,399
Oh, it's golf club covers.

278
00:11:45,043 --> 00:11:48,014
[whooping]

279
00:11:48,015 --> 00:11:49,351
Boof!

280
00:11:50,854 --> 00:11:53,860
Time for your bedtime
sweet dream routine.

281
00:11:54,729 --> 00:11:57,868
Here's your
night terror teddies,

282
00:11:57,869 --> 00:12:01,441
and I'll set the night-light
to Boogeyman Banisher.

283
00:12:02,477 --> 00:12:03,713
[Lisa giggles]

284
00:12:03,714 --> 00:12:05,750
Dad, I don't need all that.

285
00:12:05,751 --> 00:12:07,654
I don't have anxiety anymore.

286
00:12:07,655 --> 00:12:11,394
- And I have you to thank for it.
- Me?

287
00:12:11,395 --> 00:12:13,533
Yes.
Your unhinged driving

288
00:12:13,534 --> 00:12:16,304
made me face my fears
and get into go-kart racing.

289
00:12:16,305 --> 00:12:19,344
This is on you.

290
00:12:19,345 --> 00:12:21,582
[whimpers]

291
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:23,987
All my fault.
All on me.

292
00:12:25,525 --> 00:12:29,030
It's me, Lisa Mario.

293
00:12:34,542 --> 00:12:37,848
Woo-hoo! Thanks to my papa,

294
00:12:37,849 --> 00:12:39,818
I'm-a risking my life.

295
00:12:39,819 --> 00:12:43,192
And I'm a dream version
of Milhouse.

296
00:12:44,328 --> 00:12:45,496
Aah!

297
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,103
It's-a me, Wario.

298
00:12:49,104 --> 00:12:52,677
My bad parenting has lead
to your doom.

299
00:12:52,678 --> 00:12:53,446
[laughs]

300
00:12:53,447 --> 00:12:56,686
Trauma bomb! Wah!

301
00:12:56,687 --> 00:12:58,121
Aah!

302
00:12:58,122 --> 00:13:01,294
It's-a me, Wario!
It's all my fault! Wah!

303
00:13:01,295 --> 00:13:02,697
♪

304
00:13:02,698 --> 00:13:05,804
So, Paolo, you liking this vibe?

305
00:13:05,805 --> 00:13:07,574
Not enough bass?
Too much bass?

306
00:13:07,575 --> 00:13:10,279
Less bass is gonna cost.

307
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:15,790
Ketchup bottle service.

308
00:13:15,791 --> 00:13:17,828
You make it just like Milan,

309
00:13:17,829 --> 00:13:20,533
except here everyone
is fat and ugly.

310
00:13:20,534 --> 00:13:21,468
Bartolucci, I love you.

311
00:13:21,469 --> 00:13:23,806
Here is money.

312
00:13:23,807 --> 00:13:26,645
Excuse me, Signor Spaghetti,

313
00:13:26,646 --> 00:13:28,214
there's somebody at the door.

314
00:13:28,215 --> 00:13:30,554
He's not on the list and
he claims to be the principal.

315
00:13:30,555 --> 00:13:31,989
I am the principal.

316
00:13:31,990 --> 00:13:35,462
Bart Simpson,
I need to see you in my office,

317
00:13:35,463 --> 00:13:36,765
which this is.

318
00:13:36,766 --> 00:13:39,704
Bartissimo,
this polyester tie man...

319
00:13:39,705 --> 00:13:41,374
he make-a me sad.

320
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:43,077
Leave this to me.

321
00:13:43,078 --> 00:13:45,750
Seymour, why don't you
take the afternoon off?

322
00:13:45,751 --> 00:13:48,723
Here, get your mother's
tires rotated.

323
00:13:48,724 --> 00:13:51,060
That better not be a euphemism,
young man.

324
00:13:51,061 --> 00:13:53,065
Principal Skinner,
I need some help

325
00:13:53,066 --> 00:13:55,704
with the obituary
for the class hamster.

326
00:13:55,705 --> 00:13:58,474
Is the correct wording
"died by suicide"

327
00:13:58,475 --> 00:13:59,645
or "of suicide"?

328
00:13:59,646 --> 00:14:00,814
[grumbles]

329
00:14:00,815 --> 00:14:03,619
Oh, look, everyone,
it's my archrival.

330
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:07,059
Oh, enjoy your one win.

331
00:14:07,060 --> 00:14:08,863
You are only a flash in the pan.

332
00:14:08,864 --> 00:14:11,769
I am the breaded veal
in the pan.

333
00:14:11,770 --> 00:14:14,842
Paolo will be atop
the podium again.

334
00:14:14,843 --> 00:14:18,516
I'm sure you will.
You're a terrific driver.

335
00:14:19,586 --> 00:14:21,154
Oh! See how she mocks me?

336
00:14:21,155 --> 00:14:23,491
Bart, I hate her
and her whole family.

337
00:14:23,492 --> 00:14:27,032
Say cruel things about this girl
so I may agree with them.

338
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:30,406
Well, I've never met her before,
but I can tell by her vibe

339
00:14:30,407 --> 00:14:33,144
that she's an animal-kissing,
Wikipedia-editing middle child

340
00:14:33,145 --> 00:14:35,215
who burps broccoli
and farts tofu

341
00:14:35,216 --> 00:14:37,419
and won't do
her brother's homework,

342
00:14:37,420 --> 00:14:38,556
even for euros.

343
00:14:40,026 --> 00:14:43,632
And yet this girl
you have no connection to...

344
00:14:43,633 --> 00:14:44,767
she beats me.

345
00:14:44,768 --> 00:14:46,772
My thumb is raw

346
00:14:46,773 --> 00:14:48,374
from all of the doing-a this.

347
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,045
[grunts]

348
00:14:51,782 --> 00:14:53,519
That's a boof.

349
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,888
[car horn honks]

350
00:14:54,889 --> 00:14:56,526
Coming, Mom.

351
00:14:57,427 --> 00:14:58,663
I can't let you go.

352
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:00,465
Racing is too dangerous.

353
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:02,202
Dad, it's fine.

354
00:15:02,203 --> 00:15:04,273
But I had a dream last night
that I was Wario

355
00:15:04,274 --> 00:15:06,812
and I bombed you off
of Rainbow Road into oblivion.

356
00:15:06,813 --> 00:15:08,950
I'm not in danger
just because you dreamed

357
00:15:08,951 --> 00:15:13,392
a bunch of crazy stuff
from <i>Mario Kart.</i>

358
00:15:13,393 --> 00:15:14,695
What's <i>Mario Kart?</i>

359
00:15:14,696 --> 00:15:17,165
I am going to the race.

360
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,303
It's my job to keep you safe.

361
00:15:19,304 --> 00:15:22,911
You never cared about that when
you were driving like a maniac.

362
00:15:22,912 --> 00:15:25,381
Well, through some miracle
of therapy,

363
00:15:25,382 --> 00:15:28,421
I'm in the driver's seat now,
and I'm enjoying myself,

364
00:15:28,422 --> 00:15:31,695
and that's when you choose
to care about my safety?!

365
00:15:31,696 --> 00:15:34,067
You summed up things perfectly.

366
00:15:34,068 --> 00:15:35,670
So you'll stay home?

367
00:15:35,671 --> 00:15:38,175
No.
I'm in control.

368
00:15:40,046 --> 00:15:44,219
Marge, stop her.
I've never been more worried.

369
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:45,723
Well, I've never been
more relaxed.

370
00:15:45,724 --> 00:15:48,028
Hey, Mom, can I drive?

371
00:15:48,029 --> 00:15:49,197
Sure, give it a shot.

372
00:15:49,899 --> 00:15:51,368
No!

373
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,350
- ♪
- [Arborday] <i>Today,</i>

374
00:15:58,351 --> 00:15:59,785
<i>the KF-1 karting season</i>

375
00:15:59,786 --> 00:16:02,992
<i>culminates in a two-mile loop
through Springfield.</i>

376
00:16:02,993 --> 00:16:04,862
<i>A sad ruin, once home</i>

377
00:16:04,863 --> 00:16:08,636
<i>to a thriving nipple tassel
manufacturing industry.</i>

378
00:16:08,637 --> 00:16:11,475
Stupid Dad,
worried about my safety.

379
00:16:11,476 --> 00:16:14,381
Remember the time he forgot me
at a Renaissance fair?

380
00:16:14,382 --> 00:16:16,619
I had to get a ride home
from the turkey leg wench.

381
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:20,260
Oh, honey, your dad's not used
to being the one who's nervous.

382
00:16:20,261 --> 00:16:23,032
He just wants what's best
for himself.

383
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:24,568
Thanks for flying out, Bippe.

384
00:16:24,569 --> 00:16:26,172
[Italian accent]
I know Paolo cannot race

385
00:16:26,173 --> 00:16:27,841
without his secret weapon.

386
00:16:27,842 --> 00:16:28,410
<i>Andiamo!</i>

387
00:16:28,411 --> 00:16:31,583
[tools whirring]

388
00:16:35,325 --> 00:16:37,962
Aw, Bart.

389
00:16:37,963 --> 00:16:41,168
You remember that
Paolo likes gelato

390
00:16:41,169 --> 00:16:43,640
after I told you over and over

391
00:16:43,641 --> 00:16:45,444
that I like gelato.

392
00:16:45,445 --> 00:16:48,516
You are my <i>fratello</i>

393
00:16:48,517 --> 00:16:49,818
from another mamma mia.

394
00:16:49,819 --> 00:16:53,760
Oh, you must be Bart's
new Italian friend.

395
00:16:53,761 --> 00:16:54,929
Well, good luck in the race.

396
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:58,436
You're gonna need it
to beat Bart's sister.

397
00:16:58,437 --> 00:16:59,871
[gasps]

398
00:16:59,872 --> 00:17:01,576
Bart Simpson,

399
00:17:01,577 --> 00:17:03,512
you are the brother

400
00:17:03,513 --> 00:17:04,815
of Lisa Simpson?

401
00:17:04,816 --> 00:17:08,456
Um, uh, well, um, only by blood.

402
00:17:08,457 --> 00:17:10,560
<i>Traditore!</i>

403
00:17:10,561 --> 00:17:12,064
No, no.
[speaking Italian]

404
00:17:15,037 --> 00:17:16,573
[speaks Italian]

405
00:17:21,951 --> 00:17:24,122
[overlapping argument
in Italian]

406
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:39,685
Monday, Tuesday,
Thursday, Wednesday!

407
00:17:40,387 --> 00:17:43,526
Mwah.
Bart, you break-a my heart,

408
00:17:43,527 --> 00:17:44,862
like snap-a the breadstick.

409
00:17:44,863 --> 00:17:46,633
Boof.

410
00:17:49,272 --> 00:17:50,207
Aah! [grunts]

411
00:17:51,343 --> 00:17:53,145
You're not watching the race?

412
00:17:53,146 --> 00:17:56,987
I'm too worried about Lisa.
My only daughter...

413
00:17:56,988 --> 00:17:58,089
Uh, there's Maggie.

414
00:17:58,090 --> 00:18:00,894
...is rocketing around
on a flaming death-mobile!

415
00:18:00,895 --> 00:18:03,934
Why does no one else
care about Lisa's safety?

416
00:18:03,935 --> 00:18:05,336
She's fine. See?

417
00:18:05,337 --> 00:18:06,173
[Arborday]
<i>From the pole position,</i>

418
00:18:06,174 --> 00:18:08,076
<i>Lisa Simpson immediately</i>

419
00:18:08,077 --> 00:18:09,645
<i>takes the initiative.</i>

420
00:18:09,646 --> 00:18:10,881
What's initiative?

421
00:18:10,882 --> 00:18:13,085
Why does she have it?
Is it safe?

422
00:18:13,086 --> 00:18:14,388
[phone dings]

423
00:18:14,389 --> 00:18:15,790
Stupid Team Dooshé.

424
00:18:15,791 --> 00:18:16,660
Those euro jerks
forgot to remove me

425
00:18:16,661 --> 00:18:19,132
from their text thread.

426
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:21,502
<i>"Sabotaggio"?</i>

427
00:18:21,503 --> 00:18:23,539
<i>Sabotaggio?</i>

428
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:25,877
Ooh, is that some kind of
delicious spiced ham?

429
00:18:25,878 --> 00:18:27,781
It means they sabotaged
Lisa's kart!

430
00:18:27,782 --> 00:18:30,620
Oh, God, I knew
she was in danger.

431
00:18:30,621 --> 00:18:32,524
My overreacting is now just...

432
00:18:32,525 --> 00:18:34,562
[gasps] reacting.

433
00:18:34,563 --> 00:18:37,467
[Arborday] <i>It's the final lap of
the Springfield Little Grand Prix,</i>

434
00:18:37,468 --> 00:18:39,705
<i>and the karts are tighter
than a royal corgi's collar</i>

435
00:18:39,706 --> 00:18:42,811
<i>as they head into Lard Lad turn.</i>

436
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:44,848
<i>Perfecto,</i> Team Dooshé.

437
00:18:44,849 --> 00:18:47,855
You loosened all the bolts
on Lisa's kart. Boof!

438
00:18:50,828 --> 00:18:53,266
[Arborday]
<i>We have contact!</i>

439
00:18:55,204 --> 00:18:58,610
In the storm,
I am the calm at the center.

440
00:19:00,915 --> 00:19:04,422
Why is her wheel
not-a falling off?

441
00:19:04,423 --> 00:19:06,559
Aah!

442
00:19:08,463 --> 00:19:09,798
<i>Sabotaggio.</i>

443
00:19:09,799 --> 00:19:12,537
Okay, missing a wheel,
no brakes,

444
00:19:12,538 --> 00:19:15,410
still in control.

445
00:19:15,411 --> 00:19:17,680
Okay, now I'm not in control,

446
00:19:17,681 --> 00:19:19,384
but still calm.

447
00:19:19,385 --> 00:19:22,457
Wow, I have a great therapist.

448
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:24,095
She's gonna die!

449
00:19:28,003 --> 00:19:29,437
Marge, I learned my lesson.
I was right.

450
00:19:29,438 --> 00:19:31,876
Lisa's not safe.

451
00:19:32,645 --> 00:19:34,615
Aah!
<i>Sabotaggio!</i>

452
00:19:40,795 --> 00:19:43,833
- Dad!
- Don't worry, sweetie.

453
00:19:43,834 --> 00:19:45,069
I'm gonna get you
out of this mess

454
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:46,839
the way I got you
into this mess:

455
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:50,080
by driving like a maniac!

456
00:19:52,585 --> 00:19:54,255
Stay behind me.

457
00:19:56,025 --> 00:19:58,029
Aw, you're brake checking me.

458
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:02,338
But now I'm brake checking
with love.

459
00:20:05,210 --> 00:20:06,779
Oh! I-a lose.

460
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:10,353
This sport is stupid-o.

461
00:20:10,354 --> 00:20:12,791
And now I fade away to Ibiza

462
00:20:12,792 --> 00:20:16,632
to a quiet life as a beach DJ.

463
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:18,703
Boof.

464
00:20:20,808 --> 00:20:24,514
Dad, thank you.
You've made me feel safe.

465
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:27,388
And I always will.

